scope_of_work.problem:
During a site survey it was found that 1 or both Ph1 Generator Control PLC redundancy memory cards have failed or are corrupt and automatic switching between PLC A and PLC B is not likely to be achieved. The equipment is no longer supported and 
spares are difficult to obtain and on long lead times.
scope_of_work.scope:
• Supply of an RX3i CRU320 CPU
• CPU to be upgraded to the latest firmware and install the IBM software in it
• Revert the two RMX128 back to their latest firmware and run the whole thing on the bench 
to prove all is OK
• Attend site and swap out one of the CPU’s with the replacement, also installing the RMX 
card at the same time. We can then run it for a few days to ensure all is well. (This is the 
same position that you are in now)
• Upgrade of the older CPU just taken out to the latest revision.
• Do the same with the other standby CPU, giving site a complete upgraded firmware system 
so that the RMX cards work correctly 
• The remaining CPU will be left on site as a spare
scope_of_work.justification:
Currently, in the event of the Ph1 Generator Control System PLC - A failing, PLC - B will not automatically take over control. If it occurred during a mains fail, manual intervention is required which could take up to 90 minutes to complete. Phase 1 
Building Services could be without power to chillers, pumps, cooling towers and boilers for this period of time, thus the Ph1 DC suite temperatures will rise and IBM customer business equipment is at risk
scope_of_work.non_approval_effect:
Currently, in the event of the Ph1 Generator Control System PLC - A failing, PLC - B will not automatically take over control. If it occurred during a mains fail, manual intervention is required which could take up to 90 minutes to complete. Phase 1 
Building Services could be without power to chillers, pumps, cooling towers and boilers for this period of time, thus the Ph1 DC suite temperatures will rise and IBM customer business equipment is at risk
